comment.undefined: Settings to determine the uniqueness of an Object for comparison (e.g. when Diffing or computing an object Hash).
Configuration used to specify which geometry should be pulled and passed to RevitGeometry fragment.
Configuration used to specify representation to be pulled and passed to RevitRepresentation fragment.
Configuration used for adapter interaction with Revit on Remove action.
An object representing a cloned Revit type, to be pushed in order to create a new type.
Fragment containing the geometry extracted from Revit element represented by the BHoM object.
A fragment containing the information about material take off extracted on a Revit element on Pull.
Fragment containing the representation extracted from Revit element represented by the BHoM object.
Library of Revit families that can be loaded to the model.
Configuration used for adapter interaction with Revit on Push action.
Configuration used for adapter interaction with Revit on Pull action.
Wrapper for Revit family file (.rfa) that stores basic information about it such as family category, familiy type names etc.
Revit family load settings for Revit Adapter. Prototype, currently with limited functionality.
Socket connection settings for Revit Adapter.

An entity holding information about the enforced convert relationships between Revit families and BHoM types on Pull as well as mapping between Revit parameters and BHoM object properties on Push/Pull.
General settings that are applicable to all actions performed by the instance of Revit adapter.
A generic wrapper BHoM type corresponding to any Revit family type. Name of InstanceProperties corresponds to family type name, type parameter values are stored in RevitParametersToPush.
IRequest that filters all elements from a Revit link with given file name/path, Name parameter value or ElementId.

IRequest that filters all Revit elements that intersect or are contained in a Scope Box with the given name.
In case of combining this request with FilterByLink, the Scope Box will be sought for in both link document as well as the host document.
IRequest that filters all elements and types in the Revit model. This means a lot of data - please use carefully!

IRequest that filters all link instances with given file name/path, Name parameter value or ElementId from active Revit document. If link name field is left blank, all link instances in the document will be filtered.
Interface for Requests that filter elements based on parameter existence or value criterion.
IRequest that filters all elements that are contained in an energy analysis model.
IRequest that filters the active view in Revit.
IRequest that filters all elements in active Revit workset.
IRequest that filters all elements of a Revit category.
IRequest that filters all elements of given Autodesk.Revit.DB type. Information about types can be found in the Revit API documentation.
IRequest that filters elements by their ElementIds.
IRequest that filters all elements of given Revit family and type, with option to loose the search by leaving one of the input names blank.
IRequest that filters all elements of given Revit family type.
IRequest that filters elements based on given Boolean parameter value criterion.
IRequest that filters elements based on given ElementId parameter value criterion.
IRequest that filters elements the have (or do not have) a parameter with given name.
IRequest that filters elements based on given integer parameter value criterion.
IRequest that filters elements based on given floating point number parameter value criterion.
IRequest that filters elements based on given text parameter value criterion.
IRequest that filters elements contained in a given Revit Selection Set.
IRequest that filters elements by their UniqueIds.
IRequest that filters used/unused elements in a Revit document.
IRequest that filters elements specific to (owned by) a given view in Revit.
IRequest that filters all elements visible in a given Revit view.
IRequest that filters all elements in a given Revit workset.
IRequest that filters Revit families by name. If the family name is left blank, all families will be filtered.
IRequest that filters Revit family types by names of theirs and their parent family, with option to loose the search by leaving one or both of the input names blank.
IRequest that filters Revit family types that belong to a given Revit family.
IRequest that filters elements that have geometrical representation in the Revit model.
IRequest that filters Revit views by name. If the view name is left blank, all families will be filtered.
IRequest that filters all Revit views that implement a given view template.
IRequest that filters all views of given type.
IRequest that filters Revit view templates by name. If the template name is left blank, all view templates will be filtered.
IRequest that filters elements being members of selection sets, assemblies, systems etc.
Interface for Requests that filter elements based on parameter value criterion.
Interface for all fragments that carry information about Revit parameters that have been pulled or are meant to be pushed.
An object representing the definition of a Revit parameter (project parameter or shared parameter as such, not its value related to certain element or type).
An entity containing identifiers of Revit element correspondent to the BHoM object that carries it.
A BHoM wrapper class for a Revit parameter.
An entity containing parameters attached to the BHoM object that will be set to a correspondent Revit element on push.
An entity containing parameters attached to the BHoM object on pull from Revit, when a Revit element was converted to that object.
An entity defining the relationship relationship between Revit families and BHoM type, to which these families are meant to be converted on Pull.
An entity defining the relationship between property names of an object (or names of RevitParameters attached to it) and sets of their correspondent Revit element type parameter names.
An entity defining the relationship between property names of an object (or names of RevitParameters attached to it) and sets of their correspondent Revit element parameter names.
An interface for classes defining the relationship between property names of an object (or names of RevitParameters attached to it) and sets of their correspondent Revit parameter names.
An entity defining the relationship between object's property names (or names of RevitParameters attached to it) and parameter names of correspondent Revit elements.
Enum specifying detail level of representation, correspondent to level of detail in Revit.
Enumerator allowing choosing to which discipline (and corresponding namespace) should Revit elements be converted on pull.
Enumerator defining the way in which two numbers are compared.
Enumerator defining view type of Revit view. A clone of Autodesk.Revit.DB.ViewType enum.
Enumerator defining the way in which two strings are compared.
A generic wrapper BHoM type corresponding to any view-specific Revit element (drafting elements e.g. lines and hatches, tags, text notes etc.).
A wrapper BHoM type for Revit family used on Pull and Update of Revit families.
A wrapper BHoM type for Revit plan view, used to create or update Revit plans (on Push) and represent them as BHoMObjects (on Pull).

A generic wrapper BHoM type corresponding to any view-independent Revit element (model elements, e.g. duct or beam). On Push it can be used to generate or update Revit model elements that do not have a correspondent BHoM type, on Pull all Revit model elements that do not have explicit Convert method for given discipline will be converted to ModelInstance.
A wrapper BHoM type for Revit viewport, used to create or update Revit viewports (on Push) and represent them as BHoMObjects (on Pull).
A base interface for BHoM wrapper classes that can wrap Revit views.
A base interface for BHoM wrapper classes that can wrap Revit elements.
A wrapper BHoM type for Revit sheet, used to create or update Revit sheets (on Push) and represent them as BHoMObjects (on Pull).

Tolerance used for specific numerical objects or properties with a specific name.When computing Hash or the property Diffing, if the analysed object or property name is found in this collection, the corresponding tolerance is considered.

Significant digits used for specific numerical objects or properties with a specific name.When computing Hash or the property Diffing, if the analysed object or property name is found in this collection, the corresponding SignificantFigures approximation is applied.
Detail level of mesh to be pulled, correspondent to level of detail in Revit.
Detail level of representation, correspondent to level of detail in Revit.
The interface for all one-dimensional geometrical objects.
The interface for two-dimensional geometrical objects.
A polygon mesh, defined by a list of triangular or quadrilateral Faces and their Vertices.
Material composition of a Revit element correspondent to the BHoM object carrying this fragment.

Defines the make up of an object through a list of Materials as relative proportions of the total solid volume.
There must be the same number of items in both lists, assigning a single Ratio for each Material.
Discipline used on pull action. Default is Physical.
Configuration specifying which geometry should be pulled and passed to RevitGeometry fragment.
Configuration specifying representation to be pulled and passed to RevitRepresentation fragment.
Library of Revit families that can be loaded to the model.
NumberComparisonType enum representing comparison type, e.g. equality, greater, smaller etc.
NumberComparisonType enum representing comparison type, e.g. equality, greater, smaller etc.
TextComparisonType enum representing comparison type, e.g. equality, contains, starts with etc.
RevitViewType enum correspondent to Revit view type.
Requires a Fragment to contain a PersistentId, imported through an Adapter, that can be used to track an object.
Information about Revit family type or graphic type of the instance.
Location of the instance in three dimensional space.

The parent interface for all primative geometrical objects.
IGeometry implements IObject - and not IBHoMObject. Equally primative geometrical objects do not inherit from the base BHoMObject class either. As primatives, the additional base BHoM properties are omitted for both efficency and performace.
Orientation of the instance in 2 dimensional space (only X and Y vectors are relevant). Applicable only to point-based DraftingInstances. If null, a default orientation will be applied.
An ordered set of mutually orthogonal unit vectors defining three-dimensional orientation in space
An entity storing the information about Revit view type.
Information about Revit family type of the instance.
Location of the instance in in three dimensional space.
Orientation of the instance in 3 dimensional space. Applicable only to point-based ModelInstances. If null, a default orientation will be applied.
An entity storing the information about Revit viewport type.
Location of the viewport in Revit sheet space.
Defines a dimensionless location in three-dimensional space.
An entity storing the information about Revit sheet type.
